Add platform-bus NIC support for VPP via DPDK DPAA PMD.

NXP DPAA1 FMan Ethernet NICs (driver: fsl_dpa) are on the platform bus,
not PCI. This patch:

1. Adds fsl_dpa to SUPPORTED_DRIVERS and not_pci_drv lists
2. All VPP-configured interfaces use driver='dpdk' — DPAA PMD for fsl_dpa
   platform-bus NICs, standard DPDK for PCI NICs, configurable via VyOS CLI
3. Injects original_driver into iface_config so startup.conf.j2 can
   distinguish platform-bus from PCI NICs
4. startup.conf.j2: always enables dpdk_plugin.so and af_xdp_plugin.so,
   skips PCI dev entries for platform-bus NICs (DPAA bus auto-discovers),
   adds no-pci when only platform-bus NICs present
5. Lowers resource minimums for embedded ARM64 boards (2 CPUs, 256M heap)
6. Removes SSE4.2 CPU check (irrelevant on ARM64)

VPP configuration is driven entirely by VyOS CLI:
  set vpp settings interface eth3
  set vpp settings interface eth4
Ports assigned to VPP use DPDK; ports not assigned stay with the kernel.

Tested on NXP LS1046A Mono Gateway with VPP v25.10.0-48 DPAA PMD on
eth3/eth4 (10G SFP+).

